<h2>10. Final Recommendation</h2>

<div class="callout-green">
<h3>For most internal use cases &rarr; Method A (AI-Built Canvas App)</h3>
<p>Delivers a working app in 3&ndash;5 days with the least effort. Copilot generates screens automatically, Power Fx handles all business logic, and licensing is typically already covered. The design won't be pixel-perfect, but it will be professional and functional for internal Advisory staff. This is the fastest path to value.</p>

<h3>For design-critical or external-facing use cases &rarr; Method B (AI-Powered Power Pages)</h3>
<p>Achieves near-identical design by converting existing React code to vanilla HTML/CSS/JS using AI. The Kanban pipeline, quadrant matrix, and all visual components look exactly as they do today. Budget 4&ndash;7 days and the additional Power Pages license. Choose this when the visual experience or external stakeholder access is a business requirement.</p>

<h3>Hybrid: Start with A, extend with B</h3>
<p>Since both methods share the same Dataverse backend, you can launch quickly with a Canvas App for internal teams (Day 1&ndash;5), then stand up a Power Pages portal on the same data for external-facing or design-critical needs later. This &ldquo;start fast, extend later&rdquo; approach minimises upfront cost while keeping the door open.</p>
